NUMBER 485
NAME Citadel, Hallway of Warriors
INDOOR_FLOOR
FIXED_LIGHT
CALL 33
*DESCRIPTION_START
An ornate oriental rug covers the entire length of this baroque hallway.
Muted light flickers from silver leaf candleabras. Situated upon either
wall are the portraits of past and present members of the Crimson Band.
The hallway continues to the north and south, portraits of Crimson Band
members, past and present, line the walls. The only break in the artwork
is the opening in the east wall leading back into the Great Hall.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT E 2701
EXIT S 486
EXIT N 2712
ITEM 0 1308
ITEM 1 1308
ITEM 2 1308
ITEM 3 1308
ITEM 4 1308
ITEM 5 1308
ITEM 9 693
EXTEND 0 of Drizzt do'Urden
EXTEND 1 of Threnody Valerian
EXTEND 2 of Maland Pathwalker
EXTEND 3 of Fafnir Deathwing
EXTEND 4 of Jaxom LaChiere
EXTEND 5 of Jayd
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 1
Threnody Valerian, a simple aelfen female with a fighter's grace about
her. Her sea-blue eyes appear friendly and her smile contagious. She
leans on an icy rapier and there is a fiery rapier still sheathed at her 
side. Her gaze seems to linger on her wedding ring.
*DESCRIPTION_END
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 2
You see Maland Pathwalker emerging from the forest path still wielding
his blazing Crimson Naginata. His Dragon scale armor is stained with
blood but somehow you know it is not his. The mystical flame on his
forehead glows brightly as his gaze sweeps the area for more attackers.
*DESCRIPTION_END
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 3
As you look upon the portrait you see Fafnir Deathwing, former Band
Guildmaster and honorable drakin warrior.  He bears the tatoo of a
flaming katana upon his right eye and wielding a katana with a hilt
formed as a golden dragon with runes of falcon, bear, and wolf upon it.
*DESCRIPTION_END
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 4
You see Jaxom LaChiere, a tall man with flowing white hair and
brilliant blue eyes. He stands atop an open grave surrounded
on all sides by ghouls. He wields the swords of his father as
he stares across the ghouls at a dark figure with glowing eyes.
*DESCRIPTION_END
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 5
Jayd, son of Varok, a towering drakin with scales of crimson and
eyes the color of polished jade. He stands before Fayd's gates,
sword and shield in hand, daring the enemies before him to enter.
His brothers and sisters in arms can be seen standing by his side.
*DESCRIPTION_END
;
NUMBER 486
NAME Hallway of Warriors, South
INDOOR_FLOOR
FIXED_LIGHT
CALL 33
*DESCRIPTION_START
An ornate oriental rug covers the entire length of this baroque hallway. Muted
light flickers from silver leaf candleabras which are placed in such a way as
to allow future portraits to be hung here. A large tapestry hangs on the
southern wall covering it from floor to ceiling and flanked by two guardsmen.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT N 485
;You must type GO TAPESTRY if you are a CB member, or say VISITORS to take a group.
ITEM 0 250
ITEM 9 693
;----------------------Tapestry-----------------------------------------
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 0
The finely woven silk tapestry depicts a regal ceremony. In the background,
various flags and banners flutter above the Royal Palace. On either side of
Park Avenue, members of the Crimson Band stand at attention in honor of the
soon-to-be King Frederick I. In the foreground, Frederick Kentarus faces the
palace, dressed in flowing white robes and wielding a heavy bejeweled
randar sword. To his left stands the then Guildmaster of the Crimson Band,
wearing a silver tunic bearing the image of a fierce crimson eagle.
*DESCRIPTION_END
IFSAY REPORT
  IFCARRY 953 269
    RANDOM DUMMY3 1 10 0
    IFVAR DUMMY3 = 1
      ECHO ALL The guard snaps to attention and recites, "Nothing to report SIR!"
    ENDIF
    IFVAR DUMMY3 = 2
      ECHO ALL The guard snaps to attention and recites, "I've heard that Donner and Saryon have finally been banished from Fayd by decree of the king."
    ENDIF
    IFVAR DUMMY3 = 3
      ECHO ALL The guard snaps to attention and recites, "The new initates in training seem to be progressing well."
    ENDIF
    IFVAR DUMMY3 = 4
      ECHO ALL The guard snaps to attention and recites, "Our scouts report that their has been no sign of Lady High Chamberlain Riesa thus far, but all evidence seems to point towards Ilzar."
    ENDIF
    IFVAR DUMMY3 = 5
      ECHO ALL The guard snaps to attention and recites, "There was a large battle between Ilzar and Fayd, many deaths on both sides, and no apparent victor."
    ENDIF
    IFVAR DUMMY3 = 6
      ECHO ALL The guard snaps to attention and recites, "Would someone please ask the Lorekeeper to stop practicing his ambush skills on the guards?"
    ENDIF
    IFVAR DUMMY3 = 7
      ECHO ALL The guard snaps to attention and recites, "Bluefire has been seen looking awefully uncomfortable in her new armor."
    ENDIF
    IFVAR DUMMY3 = 8
      ECHO ALL The guard snaps to attention and recites, "The word is that P'thar is once again active, and has stolen the relics we seek, sir."
    ENDIF
    IFVAR DUMMY3 = 9
      ECHO ALL The guard snaps to attention and recites, "Herimos is complaining that our suppliers haven't come in, he seems worried."
      PLREVENT 1
      CONTPLREVENT
      ECHO ALL The guard groans, "Black beans and bread again."
    ENDIF
    IFVAR DUMMY3 = 10
      ECHO ALL The guard snaps to attention and recites, "Wolflings have reported that their countermeasures are in place and working satisfactorily."
    ENDIF
  ELSE
    ECHO OTHERS The guards look oddly at %N.
    ECHO PLAYER The guards look oddly at you.
  ENDIF
ENDIF
IFENTRY -1
 IFVAR INTNUM3 ! 1
    IFVAR ORG = 6
       ECHO PLAYER The guards snap to attention as you enter.
       ECHO OTHERS The guards snap to attention as %n enters.
    ENDIF
    IFVAR ORG ! 6
       ECHO PLAYER The guards seem to watch you carefully as you enter.
       ECHO OTHERS The guards seem to watch carefully as %n enters.
    ENDIF
 ENDIF
ENDIF
IFSAY Visitors
   IFCARRY 953 269
      IFVAR ITEMBIT0 = 1
         ECHO ALL A guard scans everyone carefully before moving the tapestry aside and admiting %P to the room beyond.
         AFFECT 2713
         ECHO ALL The guards snap to attention as %P is admited to the War Room.
         AFFECT 486
         MOVEGROUP 2713
      ELSE
         ECHO ALL A guard shakes his head at %N and says, "Sorry, you lack that authority to admit visitors to the War Room."
      ENDIF
   ELSE
      IFCARRY 131 989
         IFVAR ITEMBIT0 = 1
            ECHO ALL A guard shakes his head at %N and says, "Initiate %N you may neither enter the War Room nor admit visitors until you have passed all the tests."
         ELSE
            ECHO PLAYER A guard taps out a signal and a squad of soldiers drag you through the Citadel and toss you into the street.
            ECHO OTHERS A guard taps out a signal and a squad of soldiers drag %P up the Hallway of Warriors.
            POSITION LAY
            AFFECT 2713
            ECHO ALL You hear a tapping sound from the Hallway of Warriors moments before a squad of soldiers trot by to toss out an interloper.
            AFFECT 281
            ECHO ALL A squad of guards trot up to the Citadel gates from inside and toss %P out.
            AFFECT 486
            MOVEGROUP 281
         ENDIF
      ELSE
         ECHO PLAYER A guard taps out a signal and a squad of soldiers drag you through the Citadel and toss you into the street.
         ECHO OTHERS A guard taps out a signal and a squad of soldiers drag %P up the Hallway of Warriors.
         POSITION LAY
         AFFECT 2713
         ECHO ALL You hear a tapping sound from the Hallway of Warriors moments before a squad of soldiers trot by to toss out an interloper.
         AFFECT 281
         ECHO ALL A squad of guards trot up to the Citadel gates from inside and toss %P out.
         AFFECT 486
         MOVEGROUP 281
      ENDIF
   ENDIF
ENDIF
