NUMBER 1680
NAME Citadel, Initiates' Lounge
INDOOR_FLOOR
FIXED_LIGHT
CALL 33
*DESCRIPTION_START
The walls of this room are covered with a well maintained, dark oak paneling.
The floor is also hard wood, but of a lighter shade. In the center is a large
rug with a battle scene woven into it. At the far end of the room is a
massive, fieldstone fireplace, barely containing the roaring fire which has
taken the chill from the room. Over the fireplace is a large tapestry. To
the right is a large conference table surrounded by carved wooden chairs.
Several padded, reclining chairs are arranged in front of the fireplace. An
oak door leads back into the Citadel lobby.
*DESCRIPTION_END
