NUMBER 2700
NAME Citadel of the Crimson Band, Lobby
INDOOR_FLOOR
FIXED_LIGHT
CALL 33
*DESCRIPTION_START
The floor of this hall is of dark flagstone, the walls of white marble
streaked with a deep red along which hang large, colorful tapestries. High
upon the walls, torches burn in ornate sconces casting a soft light into all
corners. Apprentices, off-duty guardsmen and couriers on official business 
pass through this area intent on their business. Guards in plate armor and
bearing a crimson halberd stand stiffly at attention to either side of the 
southern passage. An oak door is inset into the western wall, and there is
an arch leading to the chapel in the eastern wall. The wide stairway to the
north leads back down to the training and parade grounds.
*DESCRIPTION_END
