NUMBER 2701
NAME Citadel, Great Hall
INDOOR_FLOOR
FIXED_LIGHT
CALL 33
*DESCRIPTION_START
The Great Hall of the citadel is the center of many a merry banquet and
celebration. A long oak table runs the length of the room, while smaller
private tables for members of the Crimson Band and honored guests stand
off to the side. There is an enormous marble fireplace in the southern 
wall with long silken tapestries to both sides. Tempting kitchen smells
waft in through an arch in the northeast corner. To the west is an ornate
hallway, on either side of which stand two guards in randar plate armor.
*DESCRIPTION_END
