NUMBER 2702
NAME Citadel, Training & Parade Grounds
OUTDOOR_FLOOR
FIXED_LIGHT
CALL 33
*DESCRIPTION_START
Before you stretches the immense training and parade grounds of the Crimson
Band. Warriors practice the arts of combat here day-in and day-out, working
with tireless instructors to keep their fighting edge. Across the grounds to
the south you can see the stairway entering the Citadel proper, flanked by a
pair of locked gates. The eastern gate leads to the stables, the western leads
to the armory. Along the western section you can see many doors that lead to
the enlisted quarters, and there are a pair of archways in the eastern wall.
Through the archways you can see skillful craftsmen shoeing horses, repairing
weapons, and making bows, arrows, and other gear needed to support an Army.
Lastly you see a spiral stairway leading to the gatehouse and the ramparts.
*DESCRIPTION_END
