NUMBER 2710
NAME Citadel, The Chapel
FIXED_LIGHT
ASTRAL
CALL 33
*DESCRIPTION_START
The simplicity of this chapel is a drastic change from the more ornate
places of worship in Fayd. The altar is made of a light stone and is
completely bare of all markings or decorations. The light in the room
is supplied by the hundreds of small candles that are set in hanging
chadeliers. Rows of benches fill the open space of the room allowing
for a large number of worshippers to be in attendance. You can see the
lobby of the Citadel through an arch in the west wall.
*DESCRIPTION_END
