EXTEND 4 of Herark Grissom
EXTEND 5 of Dane Stonebreaker
EXTEND 6 of Warsprite
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 1
Winking back at you is a Lord of Fayd and former Guildmaster of the
Band, Garin Stonehand. He is a short, muscular highlander whose beard
is flecked with gray. In one hand he wields a longsword that delivers
a light of its own and in the other a short stabbing blade.
*DESCRIPTION_END
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 2
You see Wolfbane Crag, a striking male wolfing wearing a black cloak
and a scabbard engraved 'Defender of Fayd'. He kneels before a fallen
warrior while watching over the children of Fayd during an invasion.
*DESCRIPTION_END
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 6
Opposing each other on the wall are two pictures of a small, attractive
female with polished skin. On the east wall she is smiling while playing
a flut to a rapt crowd. The western portrait shows her standing alone
against a dark host. Guildmistress Warsprite is truely a warrior-poet.
*DESCRIPTION_END
;
NUMBER 2713
NAME Crimson Band, War Room
ASTRAL
FIXED_LIGHT
CALL 33
*DESCRIPTION_START
This well lit area serves as the private meeting area for Crimson Band
members. Located within the center of the room is a large circular mirmach
table with fifteen matching chairs. Three ornately carved chairs, for the
Guildmaster, Lorekeeper and Sergeant at Arms, are located at the northern edge
of the round table. Assorted sofas, couches and overstuffed arm chairs are
scattered against the walls of the war room. Enormous maple tables line the
northern wall, to either side of the hallway entrance, and upon which are
assorted tankards and glasses filled with a variety of beverages. Apprentice
warriors scurry to and fro, ensuring that the containers remain full. Upon
the southern wall, next to a door is an old oaken kiosk.
*DESCRIPTION_END
