NUMBER 2718
NAME Citadel, Lorekeeper's Office
ASTRAL
FIXED_LIGHT
CALL 33
*DESCRIPTION_START
The office you have entered could only belong to a Lorekeeper. Except 
for the wall across from the door, the rest of the room contains shelves 
constructed from floor to ceiling. The shelves are nearly completely 
covered with books, notebooks, manuals, and the like. A rolling ladder
is attached to a rail at the top to the shelves. On the far wall hangs 
a map made of an indestructible substance depicting pre-Cataclysm Andor.
A carved rosewood desk sits in the middle of the room, a high-backed 
chair behind it. Across the desk sit two, plain wooden chairs. In the
corner you see a comfortable bed, well worn with use and rumpled.
*DESCRIPTION_END
